    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - LIFT AXLE SYSTEMS - SYSTEM OPERATION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec id="hl14019030">
        <title>SYSTEM OPERATION</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>System operation is basically the same regardless of lift axle configuration or type. The axle is
                lowered by venting the air from the lift bags and inflating the load bags. The axle is raised by venting
                the air from the load bags and inflating the lift bags (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f14019m">FIGURE 7</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f14019m" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic id="g14019m" filename="../figg14/G14019m.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitheight="192px"
                         resolution="200"/>
                <caption>Figure 7. Lift Axle Components</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. VEHICLE FRAME</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. LIFT BAG</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. LOAD BAG</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
    </svcsubsec>
